Preheat your #oven{} to 180°C. Halve, peel and chop the @Echalion Shallot{1} into ½cm pieces. Peel and grate the @Garlic Clove{1} (or use a #garlic press{}). Strip the @Thyme{2} leaves from their stalks (discard the stalks). Pick the @Oregano{1}(roughly chopped) leaves from their stalks and roughly chop (discard the stalks). Roughly chop the @Flat Leaf Parsley{½}(roughly chopped) (stalks and all). Zest the @Lemon{½}(zested) into a #bowl{} and combine with the parsley - gremolata made!

Halve the @Vine Tomatoes{2} through the equator and spread out on a lined #baking tray{}, cut side up. Sprinkle over half the oregano and a quarter of the @Grated Hard Italian Style Cheese{40%g}. Grind over plenty of @black pepper{} and drizzle with a little @oil{}. Set aside (you'll cook them later!).

Pour the @Water{¾%cup} into a large #saucepan{}. Add the @Saffron{1} powder and @Vegetable Stock Pot{1}, then bring to the boil and stir to dissolve the stock. Lower the heat. Meanwhile, heat a splash of @oil{} in another large saucepan on medium heat. Add the shallot and cook, stirring, until soft, ~{3%minutes}. Stir in the garlic, thyme and remaining oregano, cook for another ~{30%seconds}. Mix in the @Risotto Rice{175%g} and make sure it is well coated in the oil.

Add a ladleful of the hot stock to the rice and stir until almost absorbed. Repeat this process until all of the stock has been absorbed. This will take around ~{20-25%minutes}. Stir in the @Peas{1} for the last ~{5%minutes} of cooking. When ready, the risotto should be creamy, but each grain should still have a little bite.

> TIP: Taste as you go. If you run out of stock and the rice isn't cooked, add a little water and keep cooking.

Pop the tomatoes on the top shelf of your oven until tender and the cheese is golden and bubbly, ~{18-20%minutes}. Squeeze the lemon juice into a large bowl along with the @Olive Oil{1} and a pinch of @salt{pinch} and @black pepper{pinch} and combine. Leave to the side.

Stir the remaining hard Italian cheese through the finished risotto. Pop the @?Pea Shoots{1%handful} on top of the lemon and oil dressing and toss to dress the leaves. Serve the saffron risotto in #bowls{} topped with the herby baked tomatoes, a sprinkling of gremolata and the lemony pea shoot salad on the side. Enjoy!